body:
now the doc is

https://github.com/perl6/doc/blob/39539835bf833d3b8251e63a4f8504eda0e87d58/doc/Type/Grammar.pod6#L87-L101

I have try :
```
grammar RepeatChar {
    token start($character) { $character+ }
}

say RepeatChar.subparse('bbbabb', :rule('start'), :args(\('b')), :g);
say RepeatChar.subparse('bbbbbb', :rule('start'), :args(\('B')), :i);
say RepeatChar.subparse('bbbbbb', :rule('start'), :args(\('B')), :i, :pos(4));
say RepeatChar.subparse('bbbbbb', :rule('start'), :args(\('b')), :i, :pos(4));
```

but the results are too confusing.

since it says

https://github.com/perl6/doc/blob/39539835bf833d3b8251e63a4f8504eda0e87d58/doc/Type/Grammar.pod6#L60

more details about `*%opt` are needed. Otherwise not all adverbs are allowed.
